itemDescription: Irish judge and barrister, politician in New Zealand and Australia

wikipedia_page.main: George Elliott Barton (20 May 1829 – 31 May 1903) was a 19th-century lawyer and practised as a barrister in Dublin (Ireland), Melbourne (Victoria), Dunedin & Wellington (New Zealand), Sydney (New South Wales). He was appointed a judge in Dunedin and  Wellington, New Zealand.
